==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unmeet
<hw>Unmeet</hw>  <def>See <er>meet</er>.</def>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unmeet
<hw>Un*meet"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not meet or fit; not
proper; unbecoming; unsuitable; -- usually followed by
<xex>for</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Unmeet</xex> for a wife.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And all <qex>unmeet</qex> our carpet floors.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*meet"ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*meet"ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmember</ent>⟦br⟧
